#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="pli"><section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Cīvaravagga"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs0.5"
msgid ""
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs0.6"
msgid "2. Udosita(dutiyakathina)sikkhāpada"
msgstr "2. The training rule on outbuildings"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.198"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.12"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1883"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ hatthe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā "
"santaruttarena janapadacārikaṃ pakkamanti."
msgstr ""
"At that time the monks stored one of their robes with other monks and then "
"left to travel the countryside with a lower and an upper robe."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Tāni cīvarāni ciraṃ nikkhittāni kaṇṇakitāni honti."
msgstr "Because they were stored for a long time, the robes became moldy."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "Tāni bhikkhū otāpenti."
msgstr "The monks put them out in the sun."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.5"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho āyasmā ānando senāsanacārikaṃ āhiṇḍanto te bhikkhū tāni cīvarāni "
"otāpente."
msgstr ""
"While touring the dwellings, Venerable Ānanda saw the monks sunning those "
"robes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "Disvāna yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū etadavoca—"
msgstr "He asked them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "“kassimāni, āvuso, cīvarāni kaṇṇakitānī”ti?"
msgstr "“Whose moldy robes are these?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "And they told him what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "Āyasmā ānando ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "Venerable Ānanda complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.11"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ hatthe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā santaruttarena "
"janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“How can those monks store one of their robes with other monks and then "
"leave to travel the countryside with a lower and an upper robe?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1884"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.12"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando te bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato "
"etamatthaṃ ārocesi … pe …"
msgstr ""
"After criticizing those monks in many ways, Venerable Ānanda told the "
"Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.13"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ hatthe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā "
"santaruttarena janapadacārikaṃ pakkamantī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that some monks are acting like this?”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.13"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.16"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā bhikkhūnaṃ hatthe cīvaraṃ "
"nikkhipitvā santaruttarena janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissanti."
msgstr ""
"How can these foolish men store one of their robes with other monks and then "
"leave to travel the countryside with a lower and an upper robe?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.18a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1885"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.19"
msgid ""
"“Niṭṭhitacīvarasmiṃ bhikkhunā ubbhatasmiṃ kathine ekarattampi ce bhikkhu "
"ticīvarena vippavaseyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When his robe is finished and the robe-making season has ended, if a monk "
"stays apart from his three robes even for a single day, he commits an "
"offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1886"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.199"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1887"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu kosambiyaṃ gilāno hoti."
msgstr "At one time a certain monk in Kosambī was sick."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "Ñātakā tassa bhikkhuno santike dūtaṃ pāhesuṃ—"
msgstr "The relatives of that monk sent him a message:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "“āgacchatu bhadanto, mayaṃ, upaṭṭhahissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Venerable, we will attend on you.”"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.14"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "Bhikkhūpi evamāhaṃsu—“gacchāvuso, ñātakā taṃ upaṭṭhahissantī”ti."
msgstr "Other monks urged him to go, "

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "So evamāha—"
msgstr "but he said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "“bhagavatāvuso, sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ—"
msgstr "“The Master has laid down a training rule"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "‘na ticīvarena vippavasitabban’ti."
msgstr "that you cannot be apart from your three robes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "Ahañcamhi gilāno."
msgstr "Because I am sick,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.9"
msgid "Na sakkomi ticīvaraṃ ādāya pakkamituṃ."
msgstr "I’m not able to travel with all three robes,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "Nāhaṃ gamissāmī”ti."
msgstr "and therefore I cannot go.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.12"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.13"
msgid ""
"“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānassa bhikkhuno ticīvarena avippavāsasammutiṃ "
"dātuṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Monks, I allow you to give permission to a sick monk to stay apart from his "
"three robes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbā."
msgstr "And it should be given in this way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.15"
msgid ""
"Tena gilānena bhikkhunā saṃghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā "
"vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā "
"evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr ""
"After approaching the Order, the sick monk should put his upper robe over "
"one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the senior monks. He should then "
"squat on his heels, put the palms of his hands together, and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.16"
msgid "‘ahaṃ, bhante, gilāno."
msgstr "‘Venerables, I’m sick."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.17"
msgid "Na sakkomi ticīvaraṃ ādāya pakkamituṃ."
msgstr "I’m not able to travel with my three robes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.18"
msgid "Sohaṃ, bhante, saṃghaṃ ticīvarena avippavāsasammutiṃ yācāmī’ti."
msgstr "I ask the Order for permission to stay apart from my three robes.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.19"
msgid "Dutiyampi yācitabbā."
msgstr "And he should ask a second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.20"
msgid "Tatiyampi yācitabbā."
msgstr "and a third time."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.21"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṃgho ñāpetabbo—"
msgstr "A competent and capable monk should then inform the Order:"

#. </p><div class="kamma"><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1888"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.22"
msgid "‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.23"
msgid "Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu gilāno."
msgstr "This monk so-and-so is sick."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.24"
msgid "Na sakkoti ticīvaraṃ ādāya pakkamituṃ."
msgstr "He is not able to travel with his three robes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.25"
msgid "So saṃghaṃ ticīvarena avippavāsasammutiṃ yācati."
msgstr ""
"He is asking the Order for permission to stay apart from his three robes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.26"
msgid ""
"Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno ticīvarena "
"avippavāsasammutiṃ dadeyya."
msgstr ""
"If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should give permission to "
"monk so-and-so to stay apart from his three robes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.27"
msgid "Esā ñatti."
msgstr "This is the motion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1889"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.15"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.28"
msgid "Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.29"
msgid "Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu gilāno."
msgstr "This monk so-and-so is sick."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.30"
msgid "Na sakkoti ticīvaraṃ ādāya pakkamituṃ."
msgstr "He is not able to travel with his three robes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.31"
msgid "So saṃghaṃ ticīvarena avippavāsasammutiṃ yācati."
msgstr ""
"He is asking the Order for permission to stay apart from his three robes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.32"
msgid "Saṃgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno ticīvarena avippavāsasammutiṃ deti."
msgstr ""
"The Order gives permission to monk so-and-so to stay apart from his three "
"robes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.33"
msgid ""
"Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno ticīvarena avippavāsasammutiyā "
"dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;"
msgstr ""
"Any monk who approves of giving permission to monk so-and-so to stay apart "
"from his three robes should remain silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.34"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should say so."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1890"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.35"
msgid "Dinnā saṃghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno ticīvarena avippavāsasammuti."
msgstr ""
"The Order has given permission to monk so-and-so to stay apart from his "
"three robes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.36"
msgid "Khamati saṃghassa, tasmā tuṇhī,"
msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.37"
msgid "evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti."
msgstr "I will remember it thus.’"

#. </p></div><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1891"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.38"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.38a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1892"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: bhikkhusammutiyā → … sammatiyā (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.39"
msgid ""
"“Niṭṭhitacīvarasmiṃ bhikkhunā ubbhatasmiṃ kathine ekarattampi ce bhikkhu "
"ticīvarena vippavaseyya, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When his robe is finished and the robe-making season has ended, if a monk "
"stays apart from his three robes even for a single day, except if the monks "
"have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs2.40"
msgid "(<em>2</em>:<strong>21</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-np.2.3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1893"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.1.1"
msgid "Niṭṭhitacīvarasminti"
msgstr "When his robe is finished:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. This refers to robe-cloth received during the robe-making season. For details see <ref>Mv.7.2-7.12</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.1.2"
msgid ""
"bhikkhuno cīvaraṃ kataṃ vā hoti naṭṭhaṃ vā vinaṭṭhaṃ vā daḍḍhaṃ vā cīvarāsā "
"vā upacchinnā."
msgstr ""
"the monk has made a robe, or the robe-cloth has been lost, destroyed, or "
"burnt, or he has abandoned his expectation of receiving further robe-cloth."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1894"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.1.3"
msgid "Ubbhatasmiṃ kathineti"
msgstr "The robe-making season has ended:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. For an explanation of this see <ref>Mv.7.1.7</ref> and <ref>Mv.7.2-7.12</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.1.4"
msgid ""
"aṭṭhannaṃ mātikānaṃ aññatarāya mātikāya ubbhataṃ hoti, saṃghena vā antarā "
"ubbhataṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"it has ended according to one of the eight headings or the Order has ended "
"it, whichever comes first."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1895"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.1.5"
msgid "Ekarattampi ce bhikkhu ticīvarena vippavaseyyāti"
msgstr "If a monk stays apart from his three robes even for a single day:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.1.6"
msgid "saṅghāṭiyā vā uttarāsaṅgena vā antaravāsakena vā."
msgstr "from the outer robe, from the upper robe, or from the lower robe."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1896"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.1.7"
msgid "Aññatra bhikkhusammutiyāti"
msgstr "Except if the monks have agreed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.1.8"
msgid "ṭhapetvā bhikkhusammutiṃ."
msgstr "unless he has the permission of the monks."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.200"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1897"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.1.9"
msgid "Nissaggiyaṃ hotīti"
msgstr "Entailing relinquishment:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: aruṇuggamanā → aruṇuggamanena (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.1.10"
msgid "saha aruṇuggamanā nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "it becomes subject to relinquishment at dawn."

#. </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.1.11"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.1.12"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.1.13"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""
"To be expanded as in <a class=\"cr\" href=\"./pli-tv-bu-vb-np1/23-29\">"
"Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17</a>, with appropriate substitutions. …"

#. </span><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.16"></a> 
#. VAR: rattivippavutthaṃ → rattiṃ vippavutthaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.1.14"
msgid ""
"“idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ rattivippavutthaṃ aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā "
"nissaggiyaṃ,"
msgstr ""
"‘Venerables, this robe which I have stayed apart from for one day without "
"the permission of the monks is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.1.15"
