#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1898"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.2.1"
msgid "Gāmo ekūpacāro nānūpacāro."
msgstr "A village may have a single entrance or many;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.2.2"
msgid "Nivesanaṃ ekūpacāraṃ nānūpacāraṃ."
msgstr "a house may have a single entrance or many;"

#. VAR: Udosito → uddosito (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.2.3"
msgid "Udosito ekūpacāro nānūpacāro."
msgstr "an outbuilding may have a single entrance or many;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.2.4"
msgid "Aṭṭo ekūpacāro nānūpacāro."
msgstr "a watchtower may have a single entrance or many;"

#. I have here included three kinds of building—the <i lang="pli">māḷa</i>, the <i lang="pli">pāsāda</i>, and the <i lang="pli">hammiya</i>—into one category, “stilt house.” See below for an explanation.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.2.5"
msgid "Māḷo ekūpacāro nānūpacāro."
msgstr "a stilt house may have a single entrance or many;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.2.6"
msgid "Pāsādo ekūpacāro nānūpacāro."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.2.7"
msgid "Hammiyaṃ ekūpacāraṃ nānūpacāraṃ."
msgstr ""

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.17"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.2.8"
msgid "Nāvā ekūpacārā nānūpacārā."
msgstr "a boat may have a single entrance or many;"

#. The Pali term <i lang="pli">upacāra</i> may mean ‘entrance’ or ‘neighborhood,’ and thus I vary the translation depending on the context.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.2.9"
msgid "Sattho ekūpacāro nānūpacāro."
msgstr "a caravan may have a single neighborhood or many;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.2.10"
msgid "Khettaṃ ekūpacāraṃ nānūpacāraṃ."
msgstr "a field may have a single entrance or many;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.2.11"
msgid "Dhaññakaraṇaṃ ekūpacāraṃ nānūpacāraṃ."
msgstr "a threshing floor may have a single entrance or many;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.2.12"
msgid "Ārāmo ekūpacāro nānūpacāro."
msgstr "a park may have a single entrance or many;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.2.13"
msgid "Vihāro ekūpacāro nānūpacāro."
msgstr "a monastery may have a single entrance or many;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.2.14"
msgid "Rukkhamūlaṃ ekūpacāraṃ nānūpacāraṃ."
msgstr "the foot of a tree may have a single neighborhood or many;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.2.15"
msgid "Ajjhokāso ekūpacāro nānūpacāro."
msgstr "out in the open may have a single neighborhood or many."

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Exposition"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1899"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.3.1"
msgid "Gāmo ekūpacāro nāma"
msgstr "A village with a single entrance"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.3.2"
msgid "ekakulassa gāmo hoti parikkhitto ca."
msgstr "means it is an enclosed village belonging to one clan:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.3.3"
msgid "Antogāme cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antogāme vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if the robe is kept within the village, one must stay within the village."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.3.4"
msgid "Aparikkhitto hoti,"
msgstr "If the village is not enclosed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.18"></a>
#. “Of the house” is added from the commentary, see <ref>Sp.3.652.20</ref>. Without this explanation it is hard to make out whether the arm’s reach is from the house or from the robe. In each instance below I have added the commentarial explanation, found at <ref>Sp.3.652.20-3.655.10</ref>, so as to make it clear what the arm’s reach relates to.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.3.5"
msgid ""
"yasmiṃ ghare cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ ghare vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā vā "
"na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"one must stay in the house where the robe is kept, or not go beyond arm’s "
"reach of the house."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1900"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.3.6"
msgid "Nānākulassa gāmo hoti parikkhitto ca."
msgstr "An enclosed village belonging to many clans:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. <ref>Sp.3.653.6</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.3.7"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ ghare cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ ghare vatthabbaṃ sabhāye vā "
"dvāramūle vā, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if the robe is kept in a house, one must stay in that house, in the meeting "
"hall, or at the gateway to the village, or not go beyond arm’s reach of the "
"meeting hall or the gateway."

#. <ref>Sp.3.653.14</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.3.8"
msgid ""
"Sabhāyaṃ gacchantena hatthapāse cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā sabhāye vā vatthabbaṃ "
"dvāramūle vā, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If one puts aside the robe within arm’s reach while going to the meeting "
"hall, one must stay in the meeting hall, or at the gateway to the village, "
"or not go beyond arm’s reach of either."

#. <ref>Sp.3.653.29</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.3.9"
msgid ""
"Sabhāye cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā sabhāye vā vatthabbaṃ dvāramūle vā, hatthapāsā "
"vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the robe is kept in the meeting hall, one must stay in the meeting hall, "
"or at the gateway to the village, or not go beyond arm’s reach of either."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.3.10"
msgid "Aparikkhitto hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.3.11"
msgid ""
"yasmiṃ ghare cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ ghare vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā vā "
"na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"one must stay in the house where the robe is kept, or not go beyond arm’s "
"reach of the house."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1901"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.4.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa nivesanaṃ hoti parikkhittañca, nānāgabbhā nānāovarakā."
msgstr "An enclosed house belonging to one clan and having many rooms:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.4.2"
msgid "Antonivesane cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antonivesane vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept in the house, one must stay within the house."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.4.3"
msgid "Aparikkhittaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. <ref>Sp.3.654.7</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.4.4"
msgid ""
"yasmiṃ gabbhe cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ gabbhe vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā "
"vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"one must stay in the room where the robe is kept, or not go beyond arm’s "
"reach of the room."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1902"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.4.5"
msgid "Nānākulassa nivesanaṃ hoti parikkhittañca, nānāgabbhā nānāovarakā."
msgstr "An enclosed house belonging to many clans and having many rooms:"

#. </span><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.19"></a><span class="gloss">
#. <i lang="pli">Dvāramūle</i>. Explained by the commentary as “at the base of that door of the house which is common to all,” <i lang="pli">sabbesaṃ sādhāraṇe gharadvāramūle</i>, <ref>Sp.3.654.8</ref>.
#. <ref>Sp.3.654.9</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.4.6"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ gabbhe cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ gabbhe vatthabbaṃ dvāramūle vā, "
"hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if the robe is kept in a room, one must stay in that room, or at the main "
"entrance, or not go beyond arm’s reach of either."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.4.7"
msgid "Aparikkhittaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.4.8"
msgid ""
"yasmiṃ gabbhe cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ gabbhe vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā "
"vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"one must stay in the room where the robe is kept, or not go beyond arm’s "
"reach of the room."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.201"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1903"></a><span class="term">
#. <i lang="pli">Uddosita</i>. Explained in the commentary as “a hall for goods such as vehicles, etc,” <i lang="pli">yānādīnaṃ bhaṇḍānaṃ sālā</i>, see <ref>Sp.3.654.10</ref>.
#. VAR: udosito → uddosito (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.5.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa udosito hoti parikkhitto ca, nānāgabbhā nānāovarakā."
msgstr "An enclosed outbuilding belonging to one clan and having many rooms:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.5.2"
msgid "Antoudosite cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antoudosite vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept in the building, one must stay within the building."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.5.3"
msgid "Aparikkhitto hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. <ref>Sp.3.654.11</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.5.4"
msgid ""
"yasmiṃ gabbhe cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ gabbhe vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā "
"vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"one must stay in the room where the robe is kept, or not go beyond arm’s "
"reach of the room."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1904"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.5.5"
msgid "Nānākulassa udosito hoti parikkhitto ca, nānāgabbhā nānāovarakā."
msgstr "An enclosed outbuilding belonging to many clans and having many rooms:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. <ref>Sp.3.654.11</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.5.6"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ gabbhe cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ gabbhe vatthabbaṃ dvāramūle vā, "
"hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if the robe is kept in a room, one must stay in that room, or at the main "
