#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1905"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.6.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa aṭṭo hoti,"
msgstr "A watchtower belonging to one clan:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.6.2"
msgid "antoaṭṭe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antoaṭṭe vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if the robe is kept in the watchtower, one must stay within the watchtower."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.6.3"
msgid "Nānākulassa aṭṭo hoti, nānāgabbhā nānāovarakā."
msgstr "A watchtower belonging to many clans and having many rooms:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.6.4"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ gabbhe cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ gabbhe vatthabbaṃ dvāramūle vā, "
"hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"one must stay in the room where the robe is kept, or at the main entrance, "
"or not go beyond arm’s reach of either."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1906"></a><span class="term">
#. The building in <ref>MS.1.1906</ref>, the <i lang="pli">māḷa</i>, is hard to distinguish from the buildings mentioned in the next two paragraphs, the <i lang="pli">pāsāda</i> and the <i lang="pli">hammiya</i>. In fact the commentary says they are all different types of <i lang="pli">pāsāda</i>, that is, different kinds of “stilt houses,” see <ref>Sp.3.654.11</ref>. What all these buildings have in common—and this is what distinguishes them from the buildings in <ref>MS.1.1901-1.1904</ref>, the <i lang="pli">nivesana</i> and the <i lang="pli">udosita</i>—is that they do not have an enclosed category. Rather than try, from a modern perspecitve, the probably futile task of naming each of these buildings, which in any case would not be very useful from a practical perspective, I have instead grouped them together as “stilt house.” For why a <i lang="pli">pāsāda</i> is a stilt house, see [ref. to internet page].
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.7.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa māḷo hoti,"
msgstr "A stilt house belonging to one clan:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.7.2"
msgid "antomāḷe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antomāḷe vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if the robe is kept in the stilt house, one must stay within the stilt house."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.7.3"
msgid "Nānākulassa māḷo hoti nānāgabbhā nānāovarakā,"
msgstr "A stilt house belonging to many clans and having many rooms:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.7.4"
msgid ""
"yasmiṃ gabbhe cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ gabbhe vatthabbaṃ dvāramūle vā, "
"hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"one must stay in the room where the robe is kept, or at the main entrance, "
"or not go beyond arm’s reach of either."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1907"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.7.5"
msgid "Ekakulassa pāsādo hoti,"
msgstr ""

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.7.6"
msgid "antopāsāde cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antopāsāde vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.7.7"
msgid "Nānākulassa pāsādo hoti, nānāgabbhā nānāovarakā."
msgstr ""

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.7.8"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ gabbhe cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ gabbhe vatthabbaṃ dvāramūle vā, "
"hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1908"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.7.9"
msgid "Ekakulassa hammiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.7.10"
msgid "Antohammiye cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antohammiye vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.7.11"
msgid "Nānākulassa hammiyaṃ hoti, nānāgabbhā nānāovarakā."
msgstr ""

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.7.12"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ gabbhe cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ gabbhe vatthabbaṃ dvāramūle vā, "
"hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.10"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1909"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.10.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa nāvā hoti."
msgstr "A boat belonging to one clan:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.10.2"
msgid "Antonāvāya cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antonāvāya vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept on the boat, one must stay on the boat."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.10.3"
msgid "Nānākulassa nāvā hoti nānāgabbhā nānāovarakā."
msgstr "A boat belonging to many clans and having many rooms:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.10.4"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ ovarake cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ ovarake vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā "
"vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"one must stay in the room where the robe is kept, or not go beyond arm’s "
"reach of the room."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1910"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.11.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa sattho hoti."
msgstr "A caravan belonging to one clan:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. According to the commentary, an <i lang="pli">abbhantara</i> is equivalent to 28 <i lang="pli">hatthas</i> (<ref>Sp.3.654.16</ref>). Following the estimate of the <i lang="pli">hattha</i> in BMC I, pp.565-566, as 50 centimeters, this gives 14 metes for the <i lang="pli">abbhantara</i> or about 100 meters for 7 <i lang="pli">abbhantaras</i>.
#. That is one <i lang="pli">abbhantara</i>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.11.2"
msgid ""
"Satthe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā purato vā pacchato vā sattabbhantarā na "
"vijahitabbā, passato abbhantaraṃ na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if the robe is kept within the caravan, one must not go further than 100 "
"meters in front of or behind the caravan, and no further than 14 meters from "
"either side."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.11.3"
msgid "Nānākulassa sattho hoti,"
msgstr "A caravan belonging to many clans:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. <ref>Sp-ṭ.2.489</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.11.4"
msgid "satthe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā hatthapāsā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if the robe is kept within the caravan, one must not go beyond arm’s reach "
"of the caravan."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1911"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.12.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa khettaṃ hoti parikkhittañca."
msgstr "An enclosed field belonging to one clan:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.12.2"
msgid "Antokhette cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antokhette vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept within the field, one must stay within that field."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.12.3"
msgid "Aparikkhittaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. <ref>Sp.3.654.26</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.12.4"
msgid "hatthapāsā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must not go beyond arm’s reach of the robe."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.12.5"
msgid "Nānākulassa khettaṃ hoti parikkhittañca."
msgstr "An enclosed field belonging to many clans:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. <ref>Sp.3.654.27</ref>.<ref>Sp-t.2.490</ref> states that staying within arm’s reach of the robe is also acceptable. The same holds for the next two categories of threshing floor and park.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.12.6"
msgid ""
"Antokhette cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā dvāramūle vā vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā vā na "
"vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if the robe is kept within the field, one must stay at the entrance to the "
"field, or not go beyond arm’s reach of the entrance or the robe."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.12.7"
msgid "Aparikkhittaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. <ref>Sp.3.654.28</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.12.8"
msgid "hatthapāsā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must not go beyond arm’s reach of the robe."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1912"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.13.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa dhaññakaraṇaṃ hoti parikkhittañca."
msgstr "An enclosed threshing floor belonging to one clan:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.13.2"
msgid "Antodhaññakaraṇe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antodhaññakaraṇe vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if the robe is kept on the threshing floor, one must stay on that threshing "
"floor."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.13.3"
msgid "Aparikkhittaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. For the threshing floor and the next category of park, arm’s reach has the same meaning as for field, see <ref>Sp.3.655.1</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.13.4"
msgid "hatthapāsā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must not go beyond arm’s reach of the robe."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.13.5"
msgid "Nānākulassa dhaññakaraṇaṃ hoti parikkhittañca."
msgstr "An enclosed threshing floor belonging to many clans:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.21"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.13.6"
msgid ""
"Antodhaññakaraṇe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā dvāramūle vā vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā vā "
"na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if the robe is kept on the threshing floor, one must stay at the entrance to "
"the threshing floor, or not go beyond arm’s reach of the entrance or the "
"robe."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.13.7"
msgid "Aparikkhittaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.13.8"
msgid "hatthapāsā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must not go beyond arm’s reach of the robe."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1913"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.14.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa ārāmo hoti parikkhitto ca."
msgstr "An enclosed park belonging to one clan:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.14.2"
msgid "Antoārāme cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antoārāme vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept within the park, one must stay within that park."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.14.3"
msgid "Aparikkhitto hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.14.4"
msgid "hatthapāsā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must not go beyond arm’s reach of the robe."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.14.5"
msgid "Nānākulassa ārāmo hoti parikkhitto ca."
msgstr "An enclosed park belonging to many clans:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.14.6"
msgid ""
"Antoārāme cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā dvāramūle vā vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā vā na "
"vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if the robe is kept within the park, one must stay at the entrance to the "
"park, or not go beyond arm’s reach of the entrance or the robe."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.14.7"
msgid "Aparikkhitto hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.14.8"
msgid "hatthapāsā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must not go beyond arm’s reach of the robe."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.202"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1914"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.15.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa vihāro hoti parikkhitto ca."
msgstr "An enclosed monastery belonging to one clan:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.15.2"
msgid "Antovihāre cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antovihāre vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if the robe is kept within the monastery, one must stay within that "
"monastery."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.15.3"
msgid "Aparikkhitto hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. <ref>Sp.3.655.2</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.15.4"
msgid ""
"yasmiṃ vihāre cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ vihāre vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā "
"vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"one must stay in the monastic dwelling where the robe is kept, or not go "
"beyond arm’s reach of that dwelling."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.15.5"
msgid "Nānākulassa vihāro hoti parikkhitto ca."
msgstr "An enclosed monastery belonging to many clans:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.15.6"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ vihāre cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ vihāre vatthabbaṃ dvāramūle vā, "
"hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"one must stay in the monastic dwelling where the robe is kept, or at the "
"main entrance to the monastery, or not go beyond arm’s reach of either."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.15.7"
msgid "Aparikkhitto hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.15.8"
msgid ""
"yasmiṃ vihāre cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ vihāre vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā "
"vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"one must stay in the monastic dwelling where the robe is kept, or not go "
"beyond arm’s reach of the dwelling."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1915"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.16.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa rukkhamūlaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "The foot of a tree belonging to one clan:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.16.2"
msgid ""
"yaṃ majjhanhike kāle samantā chāyā pharati, antochāyāya cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā "
"antochāyāya vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if the robe is kept within the area of the midday shadow of the tree, one "
"must stay within that area."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.16.3"
msgid "Nānākulassa rukkhamūlaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "The foot of a tree belonging to many clans:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. <ref>Sp.3.655.9</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.16.4"
msgid "hatthapāsā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must not go beyond arm’s reach of the robe."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1916"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.17.1"
msgid "Ajjhokāso ekūpacāro nāma"
msgstr "Out in the open with one neighborhood:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. That is, 7 <i lang="pli">abbhantaras</i>. According to the commentary, an <i lang="pli">abbhantara</i> is equivalent to 28 <i lang="pli">hatthas</i> (<ref>Sp.3.654.16</ref>). Following the estimate of the <i lang="pli">hattha</i> in BMC I, pp.565-566, as 50 centimeters, this gives 14 metes for the <i lang="pli">abbhantara</i> or about 100 meters for 7 <i lang="pli">abbhantaras</i>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.17.2"
msgid "agāmake araññe samantā sattabbhantarā ekūpacāro,"
msgstr ""
"in an uninhabited area, in the wilderness, one neighborhood is the area "
"covered by a circle with radius 100 meters."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.22"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.17.3"
msgid "tato paraṃ nānūpacāro."
msgstr ""
"</span><span class=\"term\">Many neighborhoods</strong>: <span class=\""
"gloss\">whatever lies beyond that."

#. </span>
#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.18.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations part 2"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1917"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.18.1"
msgid ""
"Vippavutthe vippavutthasaññī aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ "
"pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he has stayed apart and he perceives that he has stayed apart, then, "
"except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing "
"relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.18.2"
msgid "Vippavutthe vematiko, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he has stayed apart, but he is unsure if he has, then, except if the "
"monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and "
"confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.18.3"
msgid ""
"Vippavutthe avippavutthasaññī, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ "
"pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he has stayed apart, but he perceives that he has not, then, except if "
"the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and "
"confession."

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.23"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.18.4"
msgid "Appaccuddhaṭe paccuddhaṭasaññī … pe …"
msgstr ""
"If he has not relinquished the robe, but he perceives that he has, then, "
"except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing "
"relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.18.5"
msgid "avissajjite vissajjitasaññī …"
msgstr ""
"If he has not given away the robe, but he perceives that he has, then, "
"except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing "
"relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.18.6"
msgid "anaṭṭhe naṭṭhasaññī …"
msgstr ""
"If he has not lost the robe, but he perceives that he has, then, except if "
"the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and "
"confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.18.7"
msgid "avinaṭṭhe vinaṭṭhasaññī …"
msgstr ""
"If the robe is not destroyed, but he perceives that it is, then, except if "
"the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and "
"confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.18.8"
msgid "adaḍḍhe daḍḍhasaññī"
msgstr ""
"If the robe is not burnt, but he perceives that it is, then, except if the "
"monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and "
"confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.18.9"
msgid ""
"avilutte viluttasaññī, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the robe is not stolen, but he perceives that it is, then, except if the "
"monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and "
"confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1918"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.18.10"
msgid "Nissaggiyaṃ cīvaraṃ anissajjitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he uses a robe which should be relinquished without first relinquishing "
"it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.18.11"
msgid "Avippavutthe vippavutthasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he has not stayed apart, but he perceives that he has, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.18.12"
msgid "Avippavutthe vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he has not stayed apart, but he is unsure if he has, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.18.13"
msgid "Avippavutthe avippavutthasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If he has not stayed apart and he perceives that he has not stayed apart, "
"there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.19.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1919"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.19.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.19.2"
msgid ""
"antoaruṇe paccuddharati, vissajjeti, nassati, vinassati, ḍayhati, "
"acchinditvā gaṇhanti, vissāsaṃ gaṇhanti,"
msgstr ""
"if before dawn it has been relinquished, given away, lost, destroyed, burnt, "
"stolen, or taken on trust;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.19.3"
msgid "bhikkhusammutiyā,"
msgstr "if he has the permission of the monks;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.19.4"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.19.5"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="38"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1920"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np2:pts-cs3.19.6"
msgid "Udosita(dutiyakathina)sikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ."
msgstr "The second rule, the training rule on outbuildings, is finished."

